  "notes": [
    "BCLC staging algorithm follows a decision tree: D → C → B/A/0",
    "Stage D is checked first (ECOG >2 OR Child-Pugh C without transplant)",
    "Stage C is checked next (vascular invasion OR extrahepatic spread)",
    "Stages 0, A, B depend on tumor burden and ECOG 0",
    "Stage 0 specifically requires: single tumor ≤2cm AND ECOG 0 AND Child-Pugh A",
    "Child-Pugh scoring: A (5-6 pts), B (7-9 pts), C (10-15 pts)",
    "Milan criteria: single ≤5cm OR up to 3 tumors all ≤3cm",
    "ECOG Performance Status: 0-4 scale (0=fully active, 4=bedbound)",
    "Treatment recommendations are evidence-based from 2022 BCLC update",
    "Atezolizumab + Bevacizumab is now first-line for Stage C"
  ]
}
